#: ../../topics/tutorials/gitfs.rst:115
msgid ""
"The repositories will be searched for files by the master in the order in "
"which they are defined in the configuration, Therefore the remote "
":strong:`git://github.com/example/first.git` will be searched first, if the "
"requested file is found then it is served and no further searching is "
"executed. This means that if the file :strong:`salt://haproxy/init.sls` is "
"requested then it will be pulled from the "
":strong:`git://github.com/example/second.git` git repo. If "
":strong:`salt://haproxy/haproxy.conf` is requested then it will be pulled "
"from the third repo."
